1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel low-rank tensor completion model using a new definition of tensor p-shrinkage nuclear norm. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The proposed model can be applied to image and video data, which are commonly studied in computer vision. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper provides a statistical upper bound of recovery error for the proposed model. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper develops an efficient algorithm to solve the resulting nonconvex optimization problem. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new definition of tensor p-shrinkage nuclear norm based on tensor singular value decomposition.
